The paper deals with style transfer, which involves manipulating images to change their appearance while preserving their content. This is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The proposed method involves optimization-based techniques, which are also commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper includes a large-scale user study, which could be considered a form of human-computer interaction (cs.MM).
